# CityShop production deploy

When the user asks to push, deploy, or update production, **always** include these server commands after a successful push.

**App path:** `~/domains/cityunlock.net/cityshop`  
**Site:** https://cityunlock.net  
**Admin login (not linked publicly):** `/admin/login`

## One command (recommended)

```bash
cd ~/domains/cityunlock.net/cityshop && bash scripts/deploy-production.sh
```

## Manual steps (if script unavailable)

```bash
cd ~/domains/cityunlock.net/cityshop
git pull origin main
php -d memory_limit=-1 composer.phar install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader
php artisan migrate --force
php artisan products:index-image-colors
php artisan storage:link 2>/dev/null || true
php artisan config:cache
php artisan route:cache
php artisan view:cache
chmod -R 775 storage bootstrap/cache
```

Vite assets are committed in the repo — **no `npm run build` on the server** unless frontend was edited directly on the server.

## Fresh database reset (wipes ALL data)

Use when starting real testing with **admin only** — no demo products, sellers, or buyers.

**Local:**
```bash
php artisan cityshop:reset --force
```

**Server:**
```bash
cd ~/domains/cityunlock.net/cityshop && bash scripts/reset-production.sh
```

Default admin after reset: `admin@cityshop.com` / `password` at `/admin/login` — change password immediately.
